					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">\frac{a}{b} in TeX is something like (a)/(b) in C. Thus the assignment would translate as
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">pulse_out = &#40;pulse1 + pulse2&#41; ? 95.88/&#40;8128/&#40;pulse1 + pulse2&#41; + 100&#41; : 0;</div>
<br />And you'd probably implement this by creating a table for pulse_out where (pulse1 + pulse2) varies from 0 to 30.</div>

