				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Docs on the actual mix levels for the external chips are rather thin on the ground. I believe most things assume the external chips are linear, and mix 50/50 with the NES output.
<br />
<br />The format of your samples depends on what's actually playing them. The two most common output formats are unsigned 8-bit (0..255) and signed 16-bit (-32768..32767). You should probably be adjusting your output to fit the range of whichever your playback hardware/API wants.
<br />
<br />If your hardware actually wants 8-bit signed, then that horrible noise you got before was the value passing 128 (and thus going negative) when you added the sunsoft in. If that is the case, you should be mixing them to 0..255, and subtracting 128 before storing in soundBuffer. Your current code might still be hitting 128 occasionally, which would do the same.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

